 Port Elizabeth - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality Driver’s and Licensing Testing Centres in Korsten and Uitenhage will be closed from Tuesday due to precautions to comply with national directives to deal with the novel coronavirus, COVID-19. Warren Prins, Director of Traffic and Licensing, said alternative arrangements will be put in place to accommodate clients with scheduled driver’s and learner’s tests as well as those with licenses on the brink of expiration. A dedicated webpage on the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality website (www.nelsonmandelabay.gov.za/page/disaster-management-advisory-forum-covid-19) has been established to share numerous aspects of the Nelson Mandela Bay Disaster Management response to the pandemic. For more information go to www.sacoronavirus.co.za, the national helpline 0800 029 999 or whatsapp 060 012 3456. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 